1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:40,979
[Strange Tales of Tang Dynasty II To the West]

3
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:44,060
[Episode 36]

4
00:01:56,960 --> 00:02:00,190
[Dunhuang, Mogao Caves]

5
00:02:04,790 --> 00:02:05,590
Mogao Caves,

6
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:07,920
the place that I even dream about.

7
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:09,110
Hundreds of caves

8
00:02:09,110 --> 00:02:10,580
were dug into the cliffs,

9
00:02:10,789 --> 00:02:12,590
yet there are no signs of collapse.

10
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:13,450
It's a miracle.

11
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:16,390
In most of these caves,

12
00:02:16,390 --> 00:02:17,850
tunnels are first dug out,

13
00:02:18,050 --> 00:02:20,030
then dug diagonally upwards to form the roofs,

14
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:21,670
and then dug downwards.

15
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:24,110
The water immersion method is also used,

16
00:02:24,110 --> 00:02:26,310
which makes it both safe and easy to dig.

17
00:02:26,310 --> 00:02:27,570
It'll never collapse.

18
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:28,670
Little kid,

19
00:02:29,060 --> 00:02:30,400
you know quite a lot.

20
00:02:30,510 --> 00:02:31,700
You just arrived, right?

21
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,030
Let me tell you about it.

22
00:02:33,829 --> 00:02:34,910
Shazhou governs

23
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:37,110
the two counties of Dunhuang and Shouchang.

24
00:02:37,110 --> 00:02:38,190
The city ahead

25
00:02:38,430 --> 00:02:40,030
is both the capital of Shazhou

26
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:41,829
and the county seat of Dunhuang.

27
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:43,550
Dunhuang, the precious land,

28
00:02:43,550 --> 00:02:45,270
connects the entire Western Region.

29
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:47,230
All roads converge here.

30
00:02:47,579 --> 00:02:49,510
So envoys can be seen here

31
00:02:49,790 --> 00:02:51,990
and merchants come and go ceaselessly.

32
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:53,990
These Mogao Caves

33
00:02:54,190 --> 00:02:56,630
are the soul of Dunhuang.

34
00:02:57,110 --> 00:02:57,710
By the way,

35
00:02:57,950 --> 00:02:59,310
three hundred years ago,

36
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:00,760
there was a monk named Yue Zun

37
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:01,870
who traveled here.

38
00:03:02,670 --> 00:03:04,400
He saw this Sanwei Mountain

39
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,110
emanating myriads of golden light,

40
00:03:06,110 --> 00:03:08,170
as if 1,000 Buddhas were meditating.

41
00:03:08,550 --> 00:03:09,190
So

42
00:03:09,350 --> 00:03:11,450
on the cliff of this Mingsha Mountain,

43
00:03:11,450 --> 00:03:13,100
he carved out the first cave.

44
00:03:13,550 --> 00:03:15,110
There are sculptures in the cave,

45
00:03:15,110 --> 00:03:16,590
all extremely exquisite.

46
00:03:18,460 --> 00:03:19,510
Just the murals

47
00:03:19,510 --> 00:03:20,370
can be divided into

48
00:03:20,370 --> 00:03:22,230
portraits, narrative paintings,

49
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:23,510
and sutra paintings.

50
00:03:23,630 --> 00:03:24,290
Among them,

51
00:03:24,350 --> 00:03:25,710
narrative paintings can be divided into

52
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:26,750
Buddhism founder's stories,

53
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:27,700
etiological stories,

54
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:28,630
Jataka stories,

55
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:30,030
and historical stories.

56
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:31,310
Ruru Jataka,

57
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:33,230
Conversion of the Five Hundred Bandits,

58
00:03:33,230 --> 00:03:34,510
and Maitreya Sutra

59
00:03:34,790 --> 00:03:36,790
are some of our ultimate treasures.

60
00:03:38,070 --> 00:03:40,070
If you want detailed explanations,

61
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:41,910
why don't you pay for it?

62
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,670
He's such a good speaker.

63
00:03:47,350 --> 00:03:48,750
We should pay him.

64
00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:50,750
Here.

65
00:03:51,110 --> 00:03:51,630
Take it.

66
00:03:52,470 --> 00:03:53,070
No thanks.

67
00:03:53,430 --> 00:03:54,690
I won't take the money.

68
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:56,510
Is it too little?

69
00:03:56,829 --> 00:03:57,350
No.

70
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:59,390
I'd give a brief introduction

71
00:03:59,390 --> 00:04:00,990
to any foreign guests I meet,

72
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:02,950
to be a good host.

73
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:04,840
Only if you

74
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:06,930
want further detailed explanations

75
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,270
or a tour around

76
00:04:08,270 --> 00:04:09,230
the caves

77
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:10,520
do you need to pay me.

78
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:12,670
Then why don't you first tell us

79
00:04:12,670 --> 00:04:14,230
what's good to eat and drink

80
00:04:14,310 --> 00:04:15,030
here?

81
00:04:15,430 --> 00:04:17,430
Our most famous fruit is

82
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:18,630
the Liguang apricot.

83
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:20,079
Our delicacies include

84
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:21,029
Xi pancakes,

85
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:22,029
Sangza,

86
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:22,910
Lengrang,

87
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:23,830
donuts,

88
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:24,670
ice cream,

89
00:04:25,710 --> 00:04:26,800
hand-grabbed mutton,

90
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,910
cumin buns,

91
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,420
and Jinsha sliced chicken.

92
00:04:29,420 --> 00:04:30,830
They're all delicious.

93
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:32,390
Your introduction

94
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:33,750
made me hungry.

95
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,710
Can you accept the money now?

96
00:04:37,430 --> 00:04:38,070
No.

97
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:40,390
I can't accept the money.

98
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:42,030
I've done too little for you.

99
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:43,060
Well...

100
00:04:44,990 --> 00:04:45,950
How about this?

101
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:48,330
Take us to see

102
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:49,320
the best cave,

103
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:49,870
okay?

104
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,409
You've found the right person.

105
00:04:52,409 --> 00:04:53,010
Follow me.

106
00:04:53,550 --> 00:04:54,470
Let’s go.

107
00:05:20,470 --> 00:05:21,390
I'm Duobao.

108
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,860
If you need anything after entering the city,

109
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:24,930
you can come to me.

110
00:05:25,350 --> 00:05:27,010
Just ask any kid for Duobao,

111
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:29,040
[Duobao]

112
00:05:27,550 --> 00:05:28,650
the one who's best at

113
00:05:28,650 --> 00:05:30,120
introducing Dunhuang,

114
00:05:30,260 --> 00:05:31,320
and you can find me.

115
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:34,220
Duobao.

116
00:05:34,710 --> 00:05:35,800
Nice name.

117
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:36,710
Thank you.

118
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:39,230
In the desert ahead,

119
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:40,650
there's even a spring.

120
00:05:41,210 --> 00:05:42,850
We call it the sand well.

121
00:05:43,630 --> 00:05:45,659
But it looks like the crescent moon.

122
00:05:45,990 --> 00:05:47,940
So I secretly named it

123
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:49,630
Crescent Spring.

124
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,570
But it hasn't caught on yet.

125
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,350
Before you enter the city,

126
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:55,010
you'll go through a sand dune.

127
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:56,950
You can surf there.

128
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,400
This is a special

129
00:05:58,430 --> 00:05:59,600
custom here.

130
00:06:00,190 --> 00:06:00,990
Sand surfing?

131
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:03,930
I didn't expect Dunhuang to be so fun.

132
00:06:05,510 --> 00:06:05,990
Duobao.

133
00:06:06,670 --> 00:06:07,670
Thank you so much.

134
00:06:07,710 --> 00:06:08,310
Wait.

135
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:13,670
Take them all.

136
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:14,950
No.

137
00:06:15,430 --> 00:06:16,470
These are enough.

138
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:19,350
Take your time.

139
00:06:19,710 --> 00:06:20,570
I'll get going.

140
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:22,070
I hope I'm lucky enough

141
00:06:22,070 --> 00:06:23,180
to see you again.

142
00:06:24,910 --> 00:06:27,950
What a great youth of Tang.

143
00:06:30,910 --> 00:06:32,170
Brother, come with me.

144
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:36,110
Look.

145
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,610
This painting looks a lot like Duobao.

146
00:06:42,590 --> 00:06:44,070
It does look like him.

147
00:06:45,670 --> 00:06:47,330
Unfortunately, it's not him.

148
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:48,550
That kid's out

149
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:51,070
to make a living at such a young age.

150
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:53,590
He must be from a poor family.

151
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:55,880
He's not qualified to be on murals.

152
00:06:58,430 --> 00:06:59,370
This man

153
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:01,670
looks old

154
00:07:02,150 --> 00:07:04,030
but even painted his nails.

155
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:07,710
It's not odd.

156
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,200
Dunhuang

157
00:07:09,230 --> 00:07:11,310
pioneered fashion.

158
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:13,150
Come.

159
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:14,230
Look.

160
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:16,590
Look at this row of people.

161
00:07:17,590 --> 00:07:19,620
They're providers.

162
00:07:19,830 --> 00:07:21,430
They're also called the cave masters

163
00:07:21,430 --> 00:07:22,690
or merit masters.

164
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,010
They funded

165
00:07:24,230 --> 00:07:26,070
this Buddhist cave.

166
00:07:26,550 --> 00:07:28,790
This cave that Duobao brought us to

167
00:07:28,790 --> 00:07:30,430
should be a family cave.

168
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:31,710
A provider

169
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:34,120
is a master of the family,

170
00:07:34,670 --> 00:07:35,430
a child,

171
00:07:35,550 --> 00:07:37,500
or even a servant who is vital

172
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:39,640
to the family.

173
00:07:40,590 --> 00:07:43,770
[Provider]

174
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:56,230
[Shazhou]

175
00:07:56,970 --> 00:08:02,490
[Shazhou, Wangjing Gate]

176
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:19,350
If I'm not mistaken,

177
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:22,150
you must be Sheriff Lu from Yunding.

178
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,240
Yes, I'm Lu Lingfeng.

179
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:27,050
[Governor of Shazhou, Zhang Huang]

180
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:27,380
I'm the governor of Shazhou, Zhang Huang.

181
00:08:27,380 --> 00:08:28,040
When I heard

182
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:30,750
you'd come here upon the court's order,

183
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:33,309
I've been waiting outside the city gate every day.

184
00:08:33,309 --> 00:08:34,679
Today is the Dragon Boat Festival.

185
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:36,679
You're finally here.

186
00:08:37,429 --> 00:08:38,690
Greetings, Governor.

187
00:08:38,710 --> 00:08:40,309
Happy Dragon Boat Festival.

188
00:08:43,669 --> 00:08:44,470
What's wrong?

189
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:45,690
Well,

190
00:08:45,830 --> 00:08:46,750
because the Dragon Boat Festival

191
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:47,680
is significant,

192
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:50,000
the governor plans

193
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:52,030
to promote a new greeting.

194
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:54,590
Everyone, listen carefully.

195
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:56,050
From now on, you'll say

196
00:08:56,110 --> 00:08:58,230
"Have a safe Dragon Boat Festival."

197
00:09:06,390 --> 00:09:07,430
Dragon Boat Festival

198
00:09:07,430 --> 00:09:09,070
has existed since ancient times.

199
00:09:09,070 --> 00:09:10,440
It's a festival

200
00:09:10,910 --> 00:09:12,870
and a happy day for the people.

201
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:14,910
As a festival,

202
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,110
it's already surpassed

203
00:09:16,110 --> 00:09:17,710
its original significance.

204
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:19,590
So, on this day,

205
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:21,550
what's wrong with a greeting

206
00:09:21,550 --> 00:09:22,430
of happiness?

207
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:24,600
Why should we change it?

208
00:09:26,350 --> 00:09:28,950
As expected from a descendant of the Lu family of Fan Yang

209
00:09:28,950 --> 00:09:31,470
and Detective Di's disciple who's earned merits

210
00:09:31,470 --> 00:09:32,860
with His Majesty.

211
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:34,740
That makes sense.

212
00:09:34,830 --> 00:09:35,780
Happy

213
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:37,330
or safe,

214
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:38,640
both are blessings.

215
00:09:38,790 --> 00:09:40,520
There's no need to restrict it.

216
00:09:40,870 --> 00:09:41,470
By the way,

217
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:44,240
we temporarily don't have an administrator,

218
00:09:44,630 --> 00:09:47,560
and our military commander went to Guazhou for work.

219
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:50,230
This is Li Chi, our judicial adjutant.

220
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:53,520
[Judicial Adjutant, Li Chi]

221
00:09:52,990 --> 00:09:53,790
Greetings.

222
00:09:56,420 --> 00:09:58,670
The governor has been planning it for a year,

223
00:09:58,670 --> 00:09:59,640
but Sheriff Lu

224
00:09:59,670 --> 00:10:01,710
rejected it as soon as we met.

225
00:10:03,590 --> 00:10:04,590
As expected of

226
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:07,110
the former general of the Imperial Guards

227
00:10:07,180 --> 00:10:09,980
and former Deputy President of the Supreme Court.

228
00:10:15,510 --> 00:10:16,700
It seems

229
00:10:17,270 --> 00:10:18,930
you know me well, Minister Li.

230
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:20,270
Of course.

231
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,510
The former administrator of Shazhou

232
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:25,910
was once the magistrate of Yunding County.

233
00:10:25,910 --> 00:10:27,190
It seems he was dismissed

234
00:10:27,190 --> 00:10:28,750
because of some petty

235
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:30,810
Yunding Immortal Steps case.

236
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:32,590
A mere sheriff like you

237
00:10:33,030 --> 00:10:34,510
can be so powerful.

238
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:36,270
It really

239
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:37,870
enlightened me.

240
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:38,830
Watch it.

241
00:10:40,190 --> 00:10:41,620
I am not that powerful.

242
00:10:42,190 --> 00:10:44,050
It's just that His Majesty is wise

243
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:46,880
and the court never indulges corrupt officials.

244
00:10:47,630 --> 00:10:48,290
Governor.

245
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:49,910
Has the delegation of Kang

246
00:10:49,910 --> 00:10:51,040
arrived in Shazhou?

247
00:10:51,990 --> 00:10:52,470
Not yet.

248
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:54,730
I think it'll take a week or so.

249
00:10:56,350 --> 00:10:57,150
In my opinion,

250
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,280
Lu Lingfeng

251
00:10:59,310 --> 00:11:01,190
is just a mere sheriff,

252
00:11:01,630 --> 00:11:03,990
but he also has his family members.

253
00:11:04,590 --> 00:11:06,110
Next, let me

254
00:11:06,270 --> 00:11:07,830
introduce them to you.

255
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:09,430
Please.

256
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:11,110
This is

257
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:14,150
the former Deputy President of the Supreme Court

258
00:11:14,150 --> 00:11:17,550
and a Detective Di's disciple, Su Wuming.

259
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:20,990
I've heard a lot about you.

260
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:22,250
Greetings, Governor.

261
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:23,270
This is

262
00:11:23,580 --> 00:11:25,080
the daughter of the Assistant Minister of Personnel,

263
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,090
Pei Xijun.

264
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,710
This is a descendant of Duke of Henan Chu Suiliang,

265
00:11:28,710 --> 00:11:29,350
Chu Yingtao.

266
00:11:29,350 --> 00:11:30,010
Greetings.

267
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:32,390
This is General Xue Rengui's great-grandson,

268
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:33,240
Xue Huan.

269
00:11:33,830 --> 00:11:34,710
Lastly,

270
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,070
let me

271
00:11:36,110 --> 00:11:37,350
introduce myself.

272
00:11:40,110 --> 00:11:41,270
I'm Handsome Fed,

273
00:11:41,730 --> 00:11:44,600
the disciple of the King of Medicine Sun Simiao.

274
00:11:44,670 --> 00:11:45,550
Where are we

275
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:47,020
staying at these days?

276
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,970
Is it a banquet every three days

277
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:50,750
or every day?

278
00:11:50,770 --> 00:11:52,770
That's up to you.

279
00:11:53,670 --> 00:11:54,150
This...

280
00:11:55,030 --> 00:11:55,700
Sure.

281
00:11:56,350 --> 00:11:57,950
Mr. Fed, I've checked.

282
00:11:58,440 --> 00:12:00,510
You'll live and eat in Qiande Hall,

283
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:02,350
the best place in Shazhou.

284
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:04,390
That's more like it.

285
00:12:04,670 --> 00:12:06,300
Get someone to get the horses now!

286
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:06,870
Yes.

287
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,630
Go get the horses now.

288
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:09,230
Go.

289
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:10,980
Sheriff Lu.

290
00:12:12,310 --> 00:12:14,350
You're all Shazhou's esteemed guests.

291
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:14,830
Please.

292
00:12:15,190 --> 00:12:15,670
Please.

293
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:29,930
Everyone, come to me.

294
